      <!-- Skills & Abilities -->
      <h2 class="section">Skills &amp; Abilities</h2>
      <div class="skills-container" id="skills" contenteditable="false"><div class="skill-item"><div class="skills-heading">Technical Skills</div><span>• <strong>Business Requirements Analysis</strong>: I applied requirement gathering, process analysis, and stakeholder communication techniques during coursework to document business requirements and recommend process improvements. This directly supports the responsibilities of gathering and documenting business requirements and analysing business processes outlined in the position.</span> <span>• <strong>Data Analysis with Excel</strong>: I used Microsoft Excel to organise and analyse data for academic assignments and presentations, creating reports and documentation that align with the role's responsibilities. I am consistently working towards achieving an 80–90% academic average, demonstrating my analytical rigour.</span> <span>• <strong>Technical Problem-Solving</strong>: I developed console applications using C# that demonstrated variables, loops, methods, and object-oriented programming concepts, then tested and debugged programmes to improve functionality and performance. This experience supports the role's requirement for strong problem-solving skills and willingness to learn business analysis tools and methodologies.</span></div><div class="skill-item"><div class="skills-heading">Soft Skills</div><span>• <strong>Stakeholder Communication</strong>: I worked effectively in group projects, delivered presentations, and applied stakeholder communication during coursework to complete business analysis assignments. This capability directly supports the position's requirement for communicating with stakeholders and creating reports and documentation.</span> <span>• <strong>Analytical Thinking</strong>: I solved complex academic case studies by identifying business problems and proposing practical technology-based solutions, analysing business problems during coursework. This approach aligns with the role's emphasis on strong analytical skills for supporting process improvement projects.</span> <span>• <strong>Collaborative Teamwork</strong>: I collaborated with classmates to complete software development and business analysis assignments within deadlines, working both independently and in teams. I balanced multiple modules while consistently meeting submission deadlines, demonstrating my ability to contribute effectively in team environments required for this position.</span></div></div>
