      <h2 class="section">Achievements &amp; Awards</h2>
      <div id="achievements" contenteditable="true">• Completed Semester 1 ICT modules through Cisco Networking Academy coursework. Earned Credly digital badges as course completion badges.<br><br>• Maintain consistent academic performance in Diploma in ICT: Business Analysis program at Durban University of Technology. Working towards achieving an 80–90% academic average.<br><br>• Participate as a Cisco Networking Academy learner while pursuing diploma studies. Building a professional technology portfolio.<br><br>• Develop active LinkedIn profile as part of professional development activities. Engage in continuous self-learning through online technology courses.<br><br>• Study Business Analysis and Business Information Systems modules in diploma program. Study Application Development using C# programming language.<br><br>• Complete Financial Accounting coursework as part of ICT diploma requirements. Study Law of Life module within the program.</div>

      <!-- Projects -->
      <h2 class="section">Projects</h2>
      <div id="projects" contenteditable="true">• Business Analysis and Solution Design I analysed business problems and proposed practical technology-based solutions to address organizational challenges. I documented business requirements and recommended process improvements to enhance operational efficiency.<br><br>• C# Console Application Development I developed console applications using variables, loops, methods, arrays, and object-oriented programming principles. I tested and debugged programs to improve functionality and performance.<br><br>• Information Systems Evaluation and Reporting I evaluated information systems used within organisations to assess their effectiveness and alignment with business needs. I produced reports and presentations on digital business solutions.</div>

